Sampras Beats O'Brien in Atlanta 
Pete Sampras beat fellow American Alex O'Brien 6-2, 7-6 (7-5) in the
first round of the 315,000 U.S. dollars ATP Challenge in Atlanta on
Tuesday.
This was his first win since Sampras reclaim his status as world tennis
number one.
The tournament was a tuneup for the only major championship Sampras has
not captured, the French Open.
Third-seeded American Jim Courier was upset by Brazil's Marcio Carlsson
6-3, 2-6, 6-4, in another match.
